Those skilled in the art will recognize that the present teachings are amenable to a variety of modifications and/or enhancements. For example, although the message server implementation described above is embodied in a hardware device, it can also be implemented as a software only solution-e.g., requiring installation on an existing server. In addition, a message server or a bind pooling mechanism as disclosed herein can also be implemented as a firmware, firmware/software combination, firmware/hardware combination, or hardware/firmware/software combination. Further features, aspects and embodiments are provided below in the following items:
Item 1. A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and a communication platform in for providing translated web content, comprising the steps of:
receiving a request from a user for content in a second language translated from content in a first language from a first Internet source;
obtaining the content in the first language from the first Internet source;
dividing the content in the first language into one or more translatable components, wherein a translatable component includes a segment of text;
determining whether the one or more translatable components have been previously translated, via at least one of machine translation, human translation, and a combination thereof, into the second language and stored as translated components in a storage, wherein each segment of text is translated as a unit; and
if there are one or more translatable components previously translated and stored as translated components,
generating the content in the second language by modifying the content in the first language so that at least some translatable components are replaced with corresponding translated components, and
sending the content in the second language to the user as a response to the request.
Item 2. The method of Item 1, wherein the human translation is aided by the machine translation.
Item 3. The method of Item 1, wherein the machine translation is edited by a human translator.
Item 4. A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and a communication platform for providing translated web content, comprising the steps of:
receiving a request from a user for content in a second language translated from content in a first language accessible from a first Internet source;
obtaining the content in the first language from the first Internet source;
dividing the content in the first language into one or more translatable components, wherein a translatable component includes a segment of text;
determining whether any of the translatable components does not have a corresponding translated component stored in the storage and generated previously via at least one of machine translation, human translation, and a combination thereof;
scheduling for translation of the translatable components that do not have corresponding translated components via at least one of machine translation, human translation, and a combination thereof to generate the corresponding translated components, wherein each segment of text is translated as a unit; and
storing the corresponding translated components in the storage.
Item 5. The method of Item 4, wherein the human translation is aided by the machine translation.
Item 6. The method of Item 4, wherein the machine translation is edited by a human translator.
Item 7. A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and a communication platform for managing language translation, comprising the steps of:
accessing from an Internet source, via a publicly available network path, content in a first language;
identifying a portion of the content in the first language that is not yet translated into a second language; and
scheduling for translation of the portion of the content in the first language that is not yet translated into a second language using at least one of machine translation, human translation, and a combination thereof to produce corresponding content in the second language.
Item 8. The method of Item 7 wherein the human translation is aided by the machine translation.
Item 9. The method of Item 7, wherein the machine translation is edited by a human translator.
Item 10. A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and communication platform for facilitating selection of a preferred language associated with a website, comprising the steps of:
receiving, via the communication platform, information including information relating to a user;
analyzing automatically the received information to estimate a preferred language in which the user likely uses to view content from the website;
displaying a selector, with an available selection of a language that most closely matches the estimated preferred language, to allow the user to specify the user's preferred language with respect to the website;
storing the user's preferred language; and
redirecting the user to the website in the user's preferred language.
Item 11. The method of Item 10, wherein the information relating to the user includes at least one of a language the user agent prefers, a default language of the user agent, the user's IP address, the user's geo-location information, a cookie associated with the user, the user's demographic information, and information reflecting the user's online activities.
Item 12. The method of Item 10, wherein the information received includes at least one of the URL of the web page and a referrer URL.
Item 13. A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and communication platform for facilitating selection of a preferred language associated with a website, comprising the steps of:
receiving, via the communication platform, information including information relating to a user viewing a web page in a first language;
analyzing the received information to determine a second language that the user likely prefers to view the web page in;
if the second language differs from the first language,
displaying a selector, with an available selection of a language that most closely matches the second language, to allow the user to specify the user's preferred language with respect to the website;
storing the specified user's preferred language; and
redirecting the user to the web page in the specified user's preferred language.
Item 14. The method of Item 13, wherein the information relating to the user is received via an HTTP request.
Item 15. The method of Item 13, wherein the information received includes at least one of:
the URL of the web page,
the referrer URL,
the user agent "Accept-language" header,
the user agent language,
the user's IP address,
the user's demographic information,
the user's geo-location information, and
a cookie.
Item 16. The method of Item 13, wherein the analysis to determine the second language is based on a predefined set of information involving at least one of:
one or more domain names,
at least one language,
one or more countries and their corresponding currencies,
a set of referrer domains associated with the second language,
a set of referrer top level domains associated with the second language,
a set of referrer sub-domains associated with the second language,
one or more sets of referrer keywords or parameters associated with the second language,
a set of geographical areas associated with the second language, and a set of affinity languages associated with the second language.
Item 17. A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and communication platform for providing a translated message in telecommunications, comprising the steps of:
receiving a request for translating a current message in a first language into a current message in a second language destined for a user;
determining whether the current message in the first language has been previously translated into a corresponding message in the second language;
if the corresponding message in the second language exists,
generating the current message in the second language based on the corresponding message in the second language previously translated; and
sending the current message in the second language to the user as a response to the request.
Item 18. The method of Item 17, wherein the message in the first language complies with a first protocol and the message in the second language complies with a second protocol.
Item 19. The method of Item 17, further comprising:
if the corresponding message in the second language does not exist,
scheduling for translation of the current message in the first language;
receiving the translation of the current message in the first language;
generating the current message in the second language based on the translation of the current message in the first language; and
sending the current message in the second language to the user as a response to the request.
Item 20. The method of Item 19, wherein the translation of the current message in the first language includes the translation of at least a portion of the current message in the first language into the second language.
Item 21. The method of Item 20, wherein the step of generating the current message in the second language comprises replacing the at least a portion of the current message in the first language with the translation of the at least a portion of the current message in the first language.
Item 22. A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and communication platform for providing a translated message in telecommunications, comprising the steps of:
receiving a request for translating a current message in a first language into a translated message in a second language destined for a user;
scheduling for translation at least a portion of the current message in the first language;
receiving the translation of the at least a portion of the current message in the first language in the second language, where the translation is performed via human translation;
generating the translated message in the second language by replacing the at least a portion of the current message in the first language with the translation of the at least a portion of the current message in the first language; and
sending the translated message in the second language to the user.
Item 23. The method of Item 22, wherein the translation of the at least a portion of the current message is stored for future re-use.
Item 24. A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and communication platform for providing a translated message, comprising the steps of:
