Item 53. A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and communication platform for providing translated web content with translated Universal Resource Locators (URLs), comprising the steps of:
receiving a request from a user for content in a second language translated from content in a first language that is accessible from a first Internet source;
obtaining the content in the first language from the first Internet source;
identifying, from the content in the first language, one or more links, each represented by an original URL;
dividing each original URL into one or more translatable URL components in the first language, wherein a translatable URL component includes a segment of text;
determining whether the one or more translatable URL components in each original URL have been previously translated, via at least one of machine translation, human translation, and a combination thereof, into the second language and stored as translated URL components;
if there is at least one translatable URL component previously translated and stored as a corresponding translated URL component,
generating a translated URL in the second language for each original URL by replacing each previously translated translatable URL component in the original URL with a corresponding translated URL component;
creating the content in the second language with translated URLs by replacing the original URLs in the first language with corresponding translated URLs in the second language; and
sending the content in the second language to the user as a response to the request.
Item 54. The method of Item 53, wherein the human translation is aided by the machine translation.
Item 55. The method of Item 53, wherein the machine translation is edited by a human translator.
Item 56. A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and communication platform for managing language translation of URLs, comprising the steps of:
accessing from an Internet source, via a publicly available network path, content in a first language;
identifying, from the content in the first language, one or more links, each represented by an original URL;
dividing each original URL into one or more translatable URL components in the first language, wherein a translatable URL component includes a segment of text;
identifying at least one translatable URL component in the first language in the original URLs that is not yet translated into a second language;
scheduling for translation of the at least one translatable URL component in the first language that are not yet translated into a second language via at least one of machine translation, human translation, and a combination thereof;
generating corresponding translated URL components in the second language based on the translation of the translatable URL components;
creating a translated URL in the second language by replacing each translatable URL component in each of the original URLs with a corresponding translated URL components; and
storing the translated URL with respect to the original URL.
Item 57. The method of Item 56, further comprising the step of converting each of the translated URL components in the second language into a format capable of being used to replace a translatable URL component in the first language in an original URL.
Item 58. The method of Item 57, wherein the human translation is aided by the machine translation.
