claim.claim-text:
A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and communication platform for providing localized content with respect to a website, comprising the steps of:
receiving a request for content where the request includes information related to a user;
retrieving one or more pieces of localized content associated with at least one condition when it is determined that the at least one condition is consistent with the information related to the user, where each localized content is localized with respect to the content requested;
identifying at least one of the retrieved localized content when the information related to the user meets the associated at least one condition; and
sending the identified at least one localized content as a response to the received request for content.

A method implemented on a computer having at least one processor, storage, and communication platform for managing localization of content with respect to a web page, comprising the steps of:
designating a location of a web page where content originally intended to be displayed therein can be localized;
providing one or more versions of localized content, each of which is localized with respect to the content originally intended to be displayed at the location;
associating each version of localized content with one or more conditions, based on which the localized content can be retrieved to replace the content originally intended to be displayed at the location; and
storing the one or more versions of the localized content with the associated one or more conditions with respect to the content originally intended to be displayed at the location of the web page so that the localized content can be retrieved in the future when the one or more conditions are met.

